Patch summary:
Build native ARM64 host mkfs.erofs without EROFS multithreading.

During target-files signing on native ARM64 hosts, mkfs.erofs can wedge while
rebuilding lz4hc-compressed partition images: the process remains alive with its
worker threads asleep on futex waits, no CPU use, and no output I/O progress.

Disable EROFS_MT_ENABLED only for ARM64 host variants. This removes the
threaded compression and dfops paths from the native ARM64 host mkfs.erofs
binary, including the linux_musl_arm64 variant copied to out/host/linux-arm64.
x86 hosts keep the upstream multithreaded default.

diff --git a/Android.bp b/Android.bp
index 7ca293f..fc5f1cf 100644
--- a/Android.bp
+++ b/Android.bp
@@ -80,6 +80,19 @@ cc_defaults {
         "-DHAVE_SYSCONF",
         "-DEROFS_MT_ENABLED",
     ],
+
+    target: {
+        linux_arm64: {
+            cflags: [
+                "-UEROFS_MT_ENABLED",
+            ],
+        },
+        linux_musl_arm64: {
+            cflags: [
+                "-UEROFS_MT_ENABLED",
+            ],
+        },
+    },
 }
 
 cc_defaults {
